parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or die while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. In some cases, it can also cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while in motion
the ignition switch has a burning smell
the ignition switch has visible signs of burning or melting
the vehicle will not restart unless the key is jiggled
the ignition switch intermittently fails and blows fuses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of stopping power, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels further than usual
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks at the top of the gas tank can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor near the gas tank
fuel leaks or drips from the top of the gas tank
hissing or gurgling sound from the gas tank area
or the fuel gauge not registering accurately.
